AIM:-Write a program to implement various types of visualisation in python.


ALGORITHM
Step 1: Import pandas, matplotlib, seaborn
Step 2: Create or load dataset
Step 3: Use line plot for trend
Step 4: Use bar chart for comparison
Step 5: Use histogram for distribution
Step 6: Use scatter plot for relationship
Step 7: Use box plot for statistical summary
Step 8: Display all graphs using plt.show()
Step 9: Stop


CODE
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

data = {
    "Name": ["Tanya", "Shivani", "Sundaram", "Sajan", "Yash"],
    "Marks": [85, 90, 78, 88, 92],
    "Age": [20, 21, 19, 20, 22]
}

# Converting to DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

plt.figure()
plt.plot(df["Name"], df["Marks"], marker='o')
plt.title("Report of Students")
plt.xlabel("Name")
plt.ylabel("Marks")
plt.show()

plt.figure()
plt.bar(df["Name"], df["Marks"])
plt.title("Student's Marks")
plt.show()

plt.figure()
plt.hist(df["Marks"], bins=5)
plt.title("Marks Distribution")
plt.show()

plt.figure()
plt.scatter(df["Age"], df["Marks"])
plt.title("Age vs Marks")
plt.xlabel("Age")
plt.ylabel("Marks")
plt.show()

plt.figure()
sns.boxplot(y=df["Marks"])
plt.title("Marksheet")
plt.show()
